Aqua Aerobic classes -Water Workout

Aquatic exercise  has become a major exercise alternative in our fitness-conscious society. 
Movements are performed in chest-deep water, these programs appeal to the swimmer and non swimmer alike.
The buoyant support of the water effectively cancels approximately 90% of the weight of a person submerged to the neck. This dramatically decreases compression stress on weight bearing joints, bones, and muscles.

column30:
The VibroGym is an exciting new way to exercise that is suitable for almost everyone.

The VibroGym is an enjoyable and easy form of exercise with many benefits including, increasing your strength, losing weight or toning your body, improving your flexibility and core stability, or just improving your general health and well-being.

Whole Body Vibration has been used for many years by a wide range of people from Russian Cosmonauts through to gold medal winning Olympic athletes. And now you clients can take advantage of the benefits of the VibroGym. If you would like to read more about the research please visit www.vibrogym.com.au
